<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="836" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d836">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102H/326: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-02T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 2,
                                        1919—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your June 9 and 21 regarding Harbin.</p>
                        <p>Department giving matter careful consideration but desires consult Consul
                            Moser, expected in Washington soon, before reaching any definite
                            decision.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>